IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: THE VEBA HAS BEEN FORMED TO PROVIDE A MECHANISM FOR AUXILIARIES OF THE CALIFORNIA STATE UNIVERSITY SYSTEM TO FUND THEIR RETIREE WELFARE BENEFIT PLAN OBLIGATIONS ON A JOINT BASIS. EACH PARTICIPATING AUXILIARY HAS ADOPTED ITS OWN RETIREE WELFARE BENEFIT PLAN AND WILL FUND ITS OBLIGATIONS UNDER ITS PLAN IN THE VEBA.
IRS990.MissionDesc: THE VEBA HAS BEEN FORMED TO PROVIDE A MECHANISM FOR AUXILIARIES OF THE CALIFORNIA STATE UNIVERSITY SYSTEM TO FUND THEIR RETIREE WELFARE BENEFIT PLAN OBLIGATIONS ON A JOINT BASIS. EACH PARTICIPATING AUXILIARY HAS ADOPTED ITS OWN RETIREE WELFARE BENEFIT PLAN AND WILL FUND ITS OBLIGATIONS UNDER ITS PLAN IN THE VEBA.
IRS990.Desc: THE VEBA ENSURES ALL RETIREE MEDICAL BENEFITS FOR THE PARTICIPATING AUXILIARIES. EACH PARTICIPATING AUXILIARY WILL PAY THE INSURANCE PREMIUMS FOR ITS RETIREES. THE VEBA WILL REIMBURSE EACH AUXILIARY TO THE EXTENT DIRECTED BY THE AUXILIARY. THE VEBA INCURS EXPENSES FOR ADMINISTRATION, INVESTMENT MANAGEMENT, ACCOUNTING AND LEGAL SERVICES. THE EXPENSES WILL BE ALLOCATED TO THE PARTICIPATING AUXILIARIES' SUB-TRUST ACCOUNTS MONTHLY BASED UPON THE BALANCE IN THEIR SUB-TRUST ACCOUNT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE TRUST IS USED FOR THE PROVISION OF RETIREE HEALTH AND WELFARE BENEFITS TO PARTICIPATING EMPLOYEES THAT IS EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAX UNDER SECTIONS 501(C)(9) OF INTERNAL REVENUE CODE AND CLASSIFIED BY THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE. THE TRUST HAS ADOPTED FASB ASC TOPIC 740 THAT CLARIFIES THE ACCOUNTING FOR UNCERTAINTY IN TAX POSITIONS TAKEN OR EXPECTED TO BE TAKEN ON A TAX RETURN AND PROVIDES THAT THE TAX EFFECTS FROM AN UNCERTAIN TAX POSITION CAN BE RECOGNIZED IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ONLY IF, BASED ON ITS MERITS, THE POSITION IS MORE LIKELY THAN NOT TO BE SUSTAINED ON AUDIT BY THE TAXING AUTHORITIES. MANAGEMENT BELIEVES THAT ALL TAX POSITIONS TAKEN TO DATE ARE HIGHLY CERTAIN AND, ACCORDINGLY, NO ACCOUNTING ADJUSTMENT HAS BEEN MADE TO THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 6
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THERE IS ONE CLASS OF MEMBERS. THE MEMBERS CONSIST OF ANY AUXILIARY THAT, WITH THE CONSENT OF THE BOARD, PARTCIPATES IN THE VEBA PURSUANT TO A PARTICIPATION AGREEMENT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE EMPLOYERS MAY APPOINT OR DISMISS TRUSTEES BY MAJORITY VOTE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE VEBA MAY BE AMENDED AT ANY TIME, IN WHOLE OR PART, BY A MAJORITY VOTE OF ALL MEMBERS

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 8B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THERE ARE NO COMMITTEES WITH AUTHORITY TO ACT ON THE ORGANIZATION'S BEHALF

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: AT LEAST (2) WEEKS PRIOR TO FILING THE ANNUAL FORM 990, THE FINAL DRAFT OF THE FORM IS DISTRIBUTED TO ALL THE TRUSTEES FOR THEIR REVIEW AND COMMENT. COMMENTS OR CHANGES SUGGESTED BY THE TRUSTEES SHALL BE FORWARDED TO THE CHAIR WHO SHALL REVIEW AND DISCUSS WITH THE CPA. THE CPA SHALL REVISE THE FORM IF NECESSARY AND THEREAFTER SUBMIT THE FORM TO THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE FOR ELECTRONIC FILING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: EACH BOARD MEMBER SIGNS A CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY DISCLAIMER ANNUALLY, THE TRUSTEE REVIEWS THE DISCLAIMER. IF A CONFLICT OF INTEREST ARISES, THE BOARD MEMBER IS ASKED TO EXCUSE HIMSELF/HERSELF FROM ALL DISCUSSION AND VOTING IN THE ISSUE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAKES IT GOVERNING DOCUMENTS AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE BY PROVIDING COPIES TO THE GENERAL PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
